{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\nIncident 2731's trigger commit (10837ca88) shipped the code_review artifact feature, but it was inert in prod: the box's .env had no REVIEWBOT_TICKETS_* vars. autodeploy.sh rsync-excludes infra/compose/.env (line 88) and never re-runs fetch-secrets.sh, so NO newly-added SSM-backed env key can reach the box on deploy without a manual boot — a half-updated-deploy-path defect.\n\n## Status\nAC1 (artifacts emitted from prod reviews) is DONE and proven in prod (see comments: SSM slot populated, terraform state reconciled, fetch-secrets re-run by hand, end-to-end artifact 8e68 emitted on change 492, 2026-07-10). The SSM/terraform work was OPERATIONAL and is already complete; note the slot /rebar/prod/reviewbot-tickets-pat already exists in infra/terraform/ssm.tf (rebar_secret_params, ~line 49) with lifecycle{ignore_changes=[value]}, so 'terraform apply' is a NO-OP for its value — the operative provisioning step was 'aws ssm put-parameter --overwrite --name /rebar/prod/reviewbot-tickets-pat --type SecureString --value <PAT>', NOT terraform. This is recorded for accuracy; no terraform/SSM work remains.\n\n## Remaining work (AC2 — the only code change)\nMake autodeploy re-run fetch-secrets.sh before 'docker compose up' so new/rotated SSM-backed env keys reach the review-bot container on deploy without a manual boot.\n\nPrecise design (in infra/scripts/autodeploy.sh):\n- Add a dedicated trigger SECRETS_PATHS='infra/scripts/fetch-secrets.sh infra/terraform/ssm.tf'. Rationale: a new env key requires editing fetch-secrets.sh (to emit the leaf) and/or ssm.tf (to declare the param); NEITHER is in BOT_PATHS, so keying the refresh only off BOT_PATHS would miss exactly the env-only-change scenario AC2 names. (Pure SSM VALUE rotation with no git change is out of scope: main does not advance, so autodeploy no-ops — that path is operator-triggered, not deploy-triggered.)\n- Guard the existing review-bot redeploy block on: changed BOT_PATHS OR changed SECRETS_PATHS (so a secrets-only change still recreates the container to pick up the new .env).\n- Placement: AFTER the rsync+chown (so $DEPLOY_REPO holds the TARGET fetch-secrets.sh) and BEFORE the ':prev' tag / 'docker compose build && up'. Invoke ENV_FILE=\"$COMPOSE_DIR/.env\" bash \"$DEPLOY_REPO/infra/scripts/fetch-secrets.sh\"; then re-assert the preserved .env owner.\n- Error contract (preserves autodeploy's fail-safe, never-half-updated guarantee): fetch-secrets is fail-fast — on any SSM error it exits 1 WITHOUT touching .env. On that failure, emit an err 'secrets-fetch-failed' marker, record_backoff_failure, and exit 1 — abort the deploy BEFORE tagging :prev or building, so the running bot stays on its current image (:latest untouched, nothing to roll back). Never build/up against a stale or half-written secrets file. Runs only on an actual bot/secrets redeploy (not every 2-min tick), so no SSM quota regression.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] code_review artifacts are written + pushed from prod reviews (no 'emission failed' warnings). [DONE in prod — change 492 / artifact 8e68]\n- [ ] autodeploy.sh re-runs fetch-secrets.sh before 'docker compose up' on a BOT_PATHS OR SECRETS_PATHS change; a new SSM-backed env key reaches the box on deploy without a manual boot.\n- [ ] On fetch-secrets failure the deploy aborts fail-safe (err marker + backoff, .env intact, running bot untouched, no rollback needed).\n- [ ] Tests cover: (a) fetch-secrets runs before compose up on a secrets-only change; (b) fetch-secrets failure aborts the deploy without building.\n- [ ] File paths: infra/scripts/autodeploy.sh (the code change); infra/scripts/fetch-secrets.sh, infra/terraform/ssm.tf (referenced/triggering, unchanged).\n\n## Out of scope / follow-ups\n- Least-privilege PAT swap (broad classic repo-scope -> fine-grained contents:write only): human-mintable only; recommended, tracked separately.\n- Bug d220 (entrypoint clone write-dead on a FRESH volume): separate ticket; prod volume already converged."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784597682032779001,"uuid":"f87630eb-e3a9-44f2-a33b-1a9f10b228c7"}